msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 33"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "33. Paramparabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on eating a meal before another"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.76"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.315"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa716"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked "
"roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ paṇītānaṃ bhattānaṃ bhattapaṭipāṭi "
"adhiṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr "At that time in Vesālī people had arranged a succession of fine meals."

#. VAR: kammakārassa → kammakarassa (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Atha kho aññatarassa daliddassa kammakārassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "And a certain poor worker thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“na kho idaṃ orakaṃ bhavissati yathayime manussā sakkaccaṃ bhattaṃ karonti; "
"yannūnāhampi bhattaṃ kareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Why don’t I prepare a meal? It won’t be inferior to the meal respectfully "
"prepared by these people.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro yena kirapatiko tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then went to his boss Kira"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ kirapatikaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"“icchāmahaṃ, ayyaputta, buddhappamukhassa bhikkhusaṃghassa bhattaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I wish to prepare a meal for the Order of monks headed by the Buddha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Dehi me vetanan”ti."
msgstr "Please give me my salary.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Sopi kho kirapatiko saddho hoti pasanno."
msgstr "Because Kira also had faith and confidence,"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: abbhātirekaṃ → atirekaṃ (s1-3) | abbhatirekaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so kirapatiko tassa daliddassa kammakārassa abbhātirekaṃ vetanaṃ "
"adāsi."
msgstr "he gave the worker his salary and much extra."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that worker went to the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so daliddo kammakāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, please accept a meal from me tomorrow together with the "
"Order of monks.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Mahā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho, jānāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Do you know that the Order is large?”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Hotu → hotu me (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Hotu, bhante, mahā bhikkhusaṃgho."
msgstr "“Let the Order be large, Venerable Sir."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.316"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Bahū me badarā paṭiyattā badaramissena peyyā paripūrissantī”ti."
msgstr "I’ve prepared much jujube and also drinks mixed with jujube.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Master consented by remaining silent, and the worker understood."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.19"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"He rose from his seat, circumambulated the Master with his right side "
"towards him, and left."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa717"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū—"
msgstr "The monks heard that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"“daliddena kira kammakārena svātanāya buddhappamukho bhikkhusaṃgho "
"nimantito, badaramissena peyyā paripūrissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"a poor worker had invited the Order of monks headed by the Buddha for a meal "
"on the following day, complete with drinks mixed with jujube."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Te kālasseva piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "And so they ate in the morning after walking for alms."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho manussā—"
msgstr "When people heard that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "“daliddena kira kammakārena buddhappamukho bhikkhusaṃgho nimantito”ti."
msgstr ""
"a poor worker had invited the Order of monks headed by the Buddha for a meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "Te daliddassa kammakārassa pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ abhihariṃsu."
msgstr "they brought much food of various kinds to him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.26"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ "
"bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—"
msgstr ""
"The following morning that worker prepared that food, and then told the "
"Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“It’s time, Venerable Sir, the meal is ready.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa718"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.28"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena tassa "
"daliddassa kammakārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"The Master robed up, took his bowl and robe, and together with the Order of "
"monks, he went to the house of that poor worker,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat in the dining hall."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro bhattagge bhikkhū parivisati."
msgstr "The worker served the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "but they kept saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "“thokaṃ, āvuso, dehi. Thokaṃ, āvuso, dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Give just a little.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.33"
msgid ""
"“Mā kho tumhe, bhante, ‘ayaṃ daliddo kammakāro’ti thokaṃ thokaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇhittha."
msgstr ""
"“Venerables, don’t accept so little because you think I’m just poor worker."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "Pahūtaṃ me khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ."
msgstr "I’ve prepared much food of various kinds."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.35"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhatha, bhante, yāvadatthan”ti."
msgstr "Venerables, please accept as much as you like.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.36"
msgid "“Na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, etaṃkāraṇā thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "“We’re not accepting so little because of that,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.37"
msgid ""
"Api ca, mayaṃ kālasseva piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjimhā; tena mayaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇhāmā”ti."
msgstr "but because we ate in the morning after walking for alms.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.317"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa719"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.38"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That poor worker complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.39"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhadantā mayā nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Venerables eat elsewhere when invited by me?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.40"
msgid "Na cāhaṃ paṭibalo yāvadatthaṃ dātun”ti?"
msgstr "Am I not able to give as much as they need?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.77"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa720"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.41"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa daliddassa kammakārassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa "
"vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that worker,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.42"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.43"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.44"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks eat elsewhere when invited for a meal?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.45"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.46"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.47"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.48"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā aññatra nimantitā aññatra "
"bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "How can those foolish men eat elsewhere when invited for a meal?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.49"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.50"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.50a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa721"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.51"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats a meal before another, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa722"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs1.52"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.318"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa723"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a cetain monk became sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.2"
msgid ""
"Aññataro bhikkhu piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Another monk took some almsfood, went to that monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“bhuñjāhi, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "and told him to eat it."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "“Alaṃ, āvuso, atthi me bhattapaccāsā”ti."
msgstr "“I can’t; I’m expecting another meal.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: ussūre → ussūrena (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhuno piṇḍapāto ussūre āharīyittha."
msgstr "But that almsfood only arrived after midday,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "So bhikkhu na cittarūpaṃ bhuñji."
msgstr "and that monk did not eat as much as he had intended."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat a meal before another."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.10a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa724"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats a meal before another, unless there is an appropriate "
"reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa725"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa726"></a> 
#. VAR: paṭiyādetvā → paṭiyādāpetvā (si, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvaradānasamaye sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyādetvā "
"bhikkhū nimantenti—"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards, during the robe-giving season, people prepared a meal "
"together with robe-cloth and then invited the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We wish to offer you a meal and give you robe-cloth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.3"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā "
"paramparabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating a meal before another and "
"being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.4"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "As a result they only obtained a small amount of robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.6"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another during the robe-giving "
"season."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.7"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.7a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa727"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats a meal before another, unless there is an appropriate "
"reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.9"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.10"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa728"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.11"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.11a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa729"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.12"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvarakārake bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards people invited monks who were making a robe for a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.13"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā "
"paramparabhojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating a meal before another and "
"being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.14"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.15"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another when you are making a robe."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.16"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa730"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.17"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats a meal before another, unless there is an appropriate "
"reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.18"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.19"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.20"
msgid "(<em>33</em>:<strong>82</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa731"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs3.21"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fifth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.78"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa732"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āyasmatā "
"ānandena pacchāsamaṇena yena aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards the Master robed up in the morning, took his bowl and  robe, "
"and went to a certain family with Venerable Ānanda as his attendant."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.319"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "He sat down on the prepared seat,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.3"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā bhagavato ca āyasmato ca ānandassa bhojanaṃ adaṃsu."
msgstr "and the people there gave staple food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.4"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggaṇhāti."
msgstr "Being afraid of wrongdoing, Ānanda did not accept it."

#. VAR: Gaṇhāhi → patigaṇhāhi (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.5"
msgid "“Gaṇhāhi, ānandā”ti."
msgstr "The Master said, “Accept it, Ānanda.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.6"
msgid "“Alaṃ, bhagavā, atthi me bhattapaccāsā”ti."
msgstr "“I can’t, Master, I’m expecting another meal.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.7"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, vikappetvā gaṇhāhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Ānanda, transfer that meal to someone else and then receive "
"this.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—“"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule">
#. VAR: bhikkhave, vikappetvā → bhattapaccāsaṃ vikappetvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.9"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vikappetvā paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another if you transfer the other "
"meal to someone else."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.10"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, vikappetabbaṃ—"
msgstr "And, monks, this is how it should be transferred:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs4.11"
msgid "‘mayhaṃ bhattapaccāsaṃ itthannāmassa dammī’”ti."
msgstr "‘I give my expected meal to so-and-so.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.33.5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.5.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa733"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.1"
msgid "Paramparabhojanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Eats a meal before another:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.2"
msgid ""
"pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantito, taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ "
"pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjati, etaṃ paramparabhojanaṃ "
"nāma."
msgstr ""
"if he has been invited to eat any of the five staple foods, and he then eats "
"any of the five staple foods elsewhere—this is called “eats a meal before "
"another.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa734"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.3"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.4"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa735"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.5"
msgid "Gilānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is sick:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.6"
msgid "na sakkoti ekāsane nisinno yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "if he is not able to eat as much as he needs in one session,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.7"
msgid "“Gilānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat a meal before another."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa736"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is the robe-giving season:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. That is, the last month of the rainy season, plus the four months of the cold season.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.9"
msgid ""
"anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā. "
"“Cīvaradānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he has not done the robe-making ceremony, he may eat a meal before "
"another during the last month of the rainy season. If he has done the robe-"
"making ceremony, he may eat a meal before another during the five month "
"period."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa737"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.10"
msgid "Cīvarakārasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is making a robe:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.11"
msgid "cīvare kayiramāne."
msgstr "if he is making a robe,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.12"
msgid "“Cīvarakārasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat a meal before another."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa738"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.13"
msgid "“Aññatra samayā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he receives food with the intention of eating it, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.1.14"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.5.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa739"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.1"
msgid ""
"Paramparabhojane paramparabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a meal before another, and he perceives it as a meal before "
"another, and he eats it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.2"
msgid ""
"Paramparabhojane vematiko, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a meal before another, but he is unsure if it is, and he eats it, "
"unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.3"
msgid ""
"Paramparabhojane naparamparabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a meal before another, but he does not perceive it as a meal before "
"another, and he eats it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa740"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.4"
msgid "Naparamparabhojane paramparabhojanasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a meal before another, but he perceives it as a meal before "
"another, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.5"
msgid "Naparamparabhojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a meal before another, but he is unsure of it, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.2.6"
msgid "Naparamparabhojane naparamparabhojanasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a meal before another, and he does not perceive it as a meal "
"before another, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.33.5.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa741"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.3"
msgid "vikappetvā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he transfers his other meal to someone else and then eats;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.320"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.4"
msgid "dve tayo nimantane ekato bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats the food from two or three invitations together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.5"
msgid "nimantanapaṭipāṭiyā bhuñjati,"
msgstr ""
"if he eats the meals in the same order that the invitations were received;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.6"
msgid "sakalena gāmena nimantito tasmiṃ gāme yattha katthaci bhuñjati,"
msgstr ""
"if he is invited by a whole village and he eats anywhere in that village;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.7"
msgid "sakalena pūgena nimantito tasmiṃ pūge yattha katthaci bhuñjati,"
msgstr ""
"if he is invited by a whole association and he eats anywhere within that "
"association;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.8"
msgid "nimantiyamāno bhikkhaṃ gahessāmīti bhaṇati,"
msgstr "if, when being invited, he says, “I’ll get almsfood;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.9"
msgid "niccabhatte,"
msgstr "if it is a regular meal invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.10"
msgid "salākabhatte,"
msgstr "if it is a meal invitation decided by drawing lots;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.11"
msgid "pakkhike,"
msgstr "if it is a half-monthly meal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.12"
msgid "uposathike,"
msgstr "if it is on the observance day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.13"
msgid "pāṭipadike,"
msgstr "if it is on the day after the observance day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.14"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,"
msgstr "if it is anything apart from the five staple foods;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.15"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.16"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa742"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:pts-cs5.3.17"
msgid "Paramparabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The third rule, the training rule on eating a meal before another, is "
"finished."

